Subtitle
16
17 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING THE OFFENSE
18 OF VIDEO VOYEURISM; TO EXTEND THE
19 STATUTE OF LIMITATIONS FOR THE OFFENSE
20 OF VIDEO VOYEURISM; AND TO MAKE AN ORDER
21 OF PROTECTION AVAILABLE TO A VICTIM OF
22 VIDEO VOYEURISM.
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
25
26 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 5-1-109(c), concerning the exceptions to
27 the statute of limitations that applies to each classification of criminal
28 offense, is amended to read as follows:
29 (c) If the period prescribed in subsection (b) of this section has
30 expired, a prosecution may nevertheless be commenced for:
31 (1) Any offense involving either fraud or breach of a fiduciary
32 obligation, within one (1) year after the offense is discovered or should
33 reasonably have been discovered by an aggrieved party or by a person who has
34 a legal duty to represent an aggrieved party and who is himself or herself
35 not a party to the offense; and
36 (2)(A) Any offense that is concealed involving felonious conduct
